<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,1173,2025]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,1389,1414]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Description</emphasis>
(
<typeStatus box="[360,462,1389,1413]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">holotype</typeStatus>
, 
<figureCitation box="[482,626,1389,1413]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1487,1510]" captionTargetBox="[188,1398,183,1460]" captionTargetId="figure-161@22.[188,1398,183,1460]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 10. Belomitra radula n. sp. A–D. Holotype, MNHN 24480, SL 19.5 mm. D. Enlarged view of the columella to show the columellar plaits. E–G. Paratype, MNHN 24481, SL 21.4 mm, G. Enlarged view of the columella to show the columellar plaits. All shells at the same scale." pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Fig. 10A–D</figureCitation>
): Shell medium-sized, strong, turriform, with high, elevated spire, consisting of 6.5 convex teleoconch whorls, slightly angulated at shoulder. Protoconch bulbous, of 1.5 strongly convex whorls, covered with very thin and narrowly spaced spiral threads. Protoconch diameter 1100 µm, height 900 µm. Protoconch-teleoconch transition marked by a weak orthocline rib. Suture impressed. Subsutural ramp well pronounced, narrow, concave. Besides inconspicuous growth lines, axial sculpture consisting of narrow, strong, closely spaced, opisthocline ribs, 23 on penultimate and 29 on last whorl, extending over whole whorl height on spire whorls, less pronounced on shell base. Spiral sculpture of distinct, narrow, sharp cords of uneven strength, covering entire shell surface and more broadly spaced on canal. On intersections with axial ribs cords form small beads, producing a nearly reticulated sculpture. Three cords on subsutural ramp of last whorl, subsutural one strongest. Aperture narrow, elongate. Outer lip evenly convex, except for a slight concavity corresponding to subsutural ramp. Columella nearly straight, with 6 very weak plaits. Callus narrow, of thin transparent glaze overlying parietal region. Siphonal notch absent. Canal short, poorly delimitated from aperture, slightly curved to left. Shell colour off-white. Periostracum very thin, colorless, tightly adherent.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
