<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,1173,2025]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,1893,1917]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Etymology:</emphasis>
From the Latin 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kantor &amp; Puillandre &amp; Rivasseau &amp; Bouchet" authorityYear="2012" box="[518,592,1893,1917]" class="Gastropoda" family="Belomitridae" genus="Belomitra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="radula">
<emphasis box="[518,592,1893,1917]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">radula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, meaning a file or scraper, in reference to the rough sculpture, used as noun in apposition.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="20" lastPageNumber="21" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,1173,2025]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,317,1965,1989]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Remarks:</emphasis>
The slightly larger 
<typeStatus box="[557,656,1966,1990]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">paratype</typeStatus>
, SAL 
<quantity box="[737,844,1965,1989]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1399999999999997" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" unit="mm" value="21.4">21.4 mm</quantity>
, with broken apical whorls, is very similar to the 
<typeStatus box="[151,252,2001,2025]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">holotype</typeStatus>
, and has a slightly more pronounced sculpture.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1436,151,247]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kantor &amp; Puillandre &amp; Rivasseau &amp; Bouchet" authorityYear="2012" box="[199,393,152,176]" class="Gastropoda" family="Belomitridae" genus="Belomitra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="radula">
<emphasis box="[199,393,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Belomitra radula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a sculpture pattern somewhat similar to that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kantor &amp; Puillandre &amp; Rivasseau &amp; Bouchet" authorityYear="2012" box="[978,1118,152,176]" class="Gastropoda" family="Belomitridae" genus="Belomitra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="reticulata">
<emphasis box="[978,1118,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">B. reticulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, from which it differs by its smaller size and more pronounced subsutural ramp. It differs from all other Indian Ocean species in overall shell shape and rough beaded sculpture.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
